    <TITLE>Spring Certification API Overview</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY>
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    This document describes the API for creating, starting and registering listeners 
    with the <a href="http://code.google.com/p/gwt-comet-streamhub/">StreamHub GWT Adapter</a>.  The adapter 
    is used for streaming live data using the <a href="http://www.stream-hub.com/">StreamHub Comet Server</a> to GWT applications.
    <h2>Examples and Tutorials</h2>
    <p>
    A quick start guide covering how to use the adapter in your GWT application is available on the front page of the <a href="http://code.google.com/p/gwt-comet-streamhub/">StreamHub GWT Adapter Project</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
    There are GWT examples available to view on the <a href="http://www.stream-hub.com/examples.html">StreamHub Examples page</a>.  
    The source code for these examples can be browsed online (<a href="http://code.google.com/p/gwt-comet-streamhub/source/browse/#svn/trunk">Browse Source Code</a>) or 
    checked out (<a href="http://code.google.com/p/gwt-comet-streamhub/source/checkout">Check Out Source Code</a>).
    </p>
    <p>
    The latest tutorials, news and getting started guides for StreamHub in general are 
    available on the <a href="http://streamhub.blogspot.com/">StreamHub Comet Blog</a>.  
    More examples are available in the SDK available to download from 
    the <a href="http://www.stream-hub.com/">StreamHub website</a>.
    </p>
    <h2>Support</h2>
    <p>
    Commercial customers should contact the StreamHub Support Team at <a href="mailto:support@stream-hub.com">support@stream-hub.com</a> quoting 
    their unique support key.
    </p>
    <p>
    Community edition users can seek help in the <a href="http://groups.google.co.uk/group/streamhub-comet-server-community">StreamHub Comet Server Community</a> on Google 
    Groups.
    </p>
  </BODY>
</HTML>
